By Laleye Dipo in Minna Terrorists on Wednesday evening again went on rampage killing unspecified number of people and setting houses ablaze in Niger State.
THISDAY was told by eyewitnesses that the terrorists burnt vehicles and shops at Ukuru village in the Bobi district of Mariga local government of the state.
A large number of villagers were also said to have been abducted by the terrorists.
It was gathered that the gunmen invaded the community in very large number, riding on motorcycles with three each on each bike and all of them carrying AK47 rifles.
Details of the attack are not known as at the time of this report.